Gordon Smale, 57-year-old president and a director of Atlantic Oil Corp., and James W. Stuckert, 51-year-old executive vice president of Hilliard & Lyons Inc., were named to the board of this gold exploration and mining company.
Mr. Smale succeeds Martin A. Clifton, who resigned from the board after Transwestern Mining Corp., a unit of Public Service Co. of New Mexico, disposed of its Royal Gold shares.
Mr. Stuckert is an addition to the board, bringing the number of directors to five. 

